===Etymology===
From {{L.}} ''[[particula]]'' ‘small part, particle’, diminutive of ''[[pars]]'' ‘part, piece’.

===Pronunciation===
*{{italbrac|[[RP]]}} {{IPA|/ˈpɑːtɪkəl/}}
*{{italbrac|US}} {{IPA|/ˈpɑːrtɪkəl/}}
*{{audio|en-us-particle.ogg|Audio (US)}}
*{{rhymes|ɑː(r)tɪkəl}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# A [[body]] with very small size; a [[fragment]].
# {{physics}} An [[elementary particle]] or [[subatomic particle]].
# {{linguistics}} A word that has a particular [[grammatical]] [[function]] but does not obviously belong to any particular [[part of speech]], such as the word ''to'' in English [[infinitive]]s.

